The paper discusses the integration of Web directories with the Semantic Web vision, which involves the use of ontologies to describe the semantics of Web resources and Web directories' categories. This suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as well as deep learning (cs.DL) and databases (cs.DB) for the construction and maintenance of Web directories. Additionally, the use of ontologies for categorization and structure suggests a potential connection to social networks and information systems (cs.SI).
